A 24- year-old man, Shamsu Sada, has been convicted by Katsina State’s Senior Magistrate Court for alleged criminal intimidate and enticed married woman in Jibia Local Government Area of the state. The prosecuting counsel, Inspector Adamu Musa, said on the 20th December, 2019 at about 13:00hrs one Yahuza Isah of Tundun Yanlihida Quarters in Katsina reported at the Control Police Station (CPS) against the suspect. That the suspect Samsu Sada, “on 22nd November, 2019 criminally, enticed his wife named Kausar Abdulahi aged 16yrs old of Tashar Tsoho Quarters, Jibia by letting her through phone that she should divorce her husband come back home and marry you, which is contrary to section 372 and 365 of Katsina penal code law.” The Suspect therefore accepted guilty of the offence. The Senior Magistrate, Abdulkarim Ahmed Umar, thereby sentenced him to pay a fine of N77,000 or in default serve one year jail term.